<H2>Package Information Window</H2>

<P>
The package information window shows more information
on the currently selected package. It is shown either
from the toolbar (the "i" icon) or the applications
menu.
</P>

<P>
The information shown in the window is
<UL>
<LI>Package - name of the package</LI>
<LI>Version - highest version available on one of the package sites</LI>
<LI>Installed - version currently installed</LI>
<LI>Section - classification of the application</LI>
<LI>Priority - how important it is for your system</LI>
<LI>Size - size of package that will be downloaded in bytes</LI>
<LI>URL - location file will be downloaded from</LI>
<LI>Source - name of the source this package was created from (if any)</LI>
<LI>Standards ver - earliest version of the packaging process that is needed to install this package</LI>
<LI>Maintainer - name and email address of the person who has created and is maintaining this package.
This is the person who has created the package for distribution, and may not be the same as the
author of the application(s)/resource(s) installed by the package</LI>
<LI>Depends - list of packages this package needs installed before if will work.
The install/upgrade process will automatically install these if they are not already installed</LI>
<LI>Conflicts - list of packages that can not be installed at the same time as this package</LI>
<LI>Recommends - list of packages that are recommended (but not essential) to be installed as well as this package</LI>
<LI>Suggests - list of packages that may be useful when used alongside or with this package</LI>
<LI>Description - full description of the package</LI>
</UL>
</P>

</BODY>
